    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1121"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1121">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">311.5754 Janko/18</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Attorney General</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-18">February 18,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>:</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">Motor Tank Vessel <hi rend="italic">Norsktank</hi> (Ex <hi
                        rend="italic">Janko</hi>) Libel of possession of Pankos Operating Company,
                    S.A. and plea of sovereign immunity—Your number Le 311.5754 Janko/6</p>
                <p>The question of immunity of the Norwegian Motor Tank Vessel <hi rend="italic"
                        >Norsktank</hi> from seizure and arrest in the above proceedings was
                    submitted to the United States District Court for the Eastern District of New
                    York and the United States Circuit Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit and
                    on February 10, 1944, the order of the Court was entered, releasing and
                    discharging the <hi rend="italic">Janko</hi> from the custody of the Court.</p>
                <p>Respectfully,</p>
                <closer>For the Attorney General, <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis M. Shea</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Assistant Attorney General</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
